  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Previous research has shown that sleep quality in hemodialysis patients is disturbed. One of
      the possible explanations is an insufficient or disturbed melatonin rhythm. Melatonin rhythm
      is regulated by exposure to light. In this feasibility study, the investigators examine the
      effects of light therapy during dialysis on sleep, melatonin rhythm and mood.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
